S: Pete shot the man in defense, and left him under the morning sun.
X: Pete made a friend with a stranger who trespassed.
Y: A stranger tried to shoot Pete.
A: The answer is neither X nor Y has more power to explain the observations. Both hypotheses are unrelated to the observations given.
pred_before : neither X nor Y has more power to explain the observations. Both hypotheses are unrelated to the observations given.
pred_after : X
pred : X

pred_after : Y
pred : Y

Q: There are two hypotheses, X and Y, to explain two observations, R and S. Which of the hypotheses X and Y has more power to explain the observations?
R: I was talking to my girlfriend and some girls came by.
S: I hugged her and let her know everything will be ok.
X: I turned and looked at the girls walking by, and my girlfriend became upset.
Y: One of my girlfriends was in a panic because she couldn't find her penny.
A: The answer is X, as it directly relates to the observations R and S. Hypothesis Y is unrelated to the observations and therefore has no power to explain them.
pred_before : X, as it directly relates to the observations R and S. Hypothesis Y is unrelated to the observations and therefore has no power to explain them.
pred_after : X
pred : X
GT : X
